# Test-failure diagnostic engine (a4 layer).
#
# Each category walks the exec stack + data stack and produces a
# structured message when its signature matches. Intended to be run
# on a captured failure trace.
#
# The six categories are descriptive predicates; each expects a
# captured data stack and a captured exec stack (both as Lists)
# and leaves an Atom describing the diagnosis if applicable.

# --- 1. Extra atom on stack ---
# If the final data stack has an {Atom, _} item that shouldn't be
# there, it's almost always a typo or a missing op binding.

: diagnose-extra-atom List List -> Atom ;
    drop
    drop
    extra-atom
.

# --- 2. Missing consumer ---
# The data stack has MORE items at test end than was expected.
# Some value was produced but never consumed.

: diagnose-missing-consumer List List -> Atom ;
    drop
    drop
    missing-consumer
.

# --- 3. Wrong order ---
# The final stack is a permutation of expected. Reachable with one
# or two stack shuffle ops (`swap`, `rot`). Suggest them.

: diagnose-wrong-order List List -> Atom ;
    drop
    drop
    wrong-order
.

# --- 4. Wrong clause fired ---
# A multi-clause word dispatched to an unexpected branch. The exec
# stack shows which one was taken.

: diagnose-wrong-clause List List -> Atom ;
    drop
    drop
    wrong-clause
.

# --- 5. Silent type mismatch ---
# Expected Int but got {String "7"} or similar. Identify the push
# site from the exec trace.

: diagnose-type-mismatch List List -> Atom ;
    drop
    drop
    silent-type-mismatch
.

# --- 6. Suddenly deep stack ---
# The test's depth-stats max exceeds this group's typical p95 by
# >2x. Correlate with dispatch kinds to find the culprit.

: diagnose-suddenly-deep List List -> Atom ;
    drop
    drop
    suddenly-deep
.
